| fp | 0.1-0.2 | Uncertainty in planet formation rate |
| ne | 2-5 planets per star | Uncertainty in number of planets per star |
| fl | 1 in 1000 planets to 1 in a million planets | Uncertainty in probability of life arising on a planet |
| fi | 1 in 1000 planets to 1 in a million planets | Uncertainty in probability of intelligent life arising on a planet |
| fc | 1% to 5% of civilizations develop detectable technology | Uncertainty in the fraction of civilizations that develop detectable technology |
| L | Up to a few thousand years for each civilization | Uncertainty in the lifetime of technological civilizations |

